* MVS Clean Shutdown Script for TK5
* Source: MVS-sysgen/sysgen/SCRIPTS/SHUTDOWN.RC
*
* Usage: From Hercules console, type:
*   script SCRIPTS/mvs_shutdown.rc
*
* Or from herc_automation.py:
*   h.send_herc('script scripts/mvs_shutdown.rc')
*
* This performs a graceful MVS shutdown sequence:
*   1. Stop JES2 initiators
*   2. Stop printers/readers/punches
*   3. Stop TSO
*   4. Stop VTAM
*   5. Halt Hercules
*
* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

* Set up automated responses for shutdown messages
hao clear
hao tgt HASP099
hao cmd script scripts/pjes2
hao tgt HASP085
hao cmd script scripts/zeod
hao tgt IEE334I
hao cmd script scripts/quiesce
hao tgt HHC00814I Processor CP00: SIGP Stop
hao cmd script scripts/poweroff
hao tgt HHC00814I Processor CP01: SIGP Stop
hao cmd script scripts/poweroff
hao tgt ([0-9]{2}) IKT010D
hao cmd /R $1,FSTOP

* Cancel all pending automatic commands
/$CA,ALL
pause 2

* Switch SMF recording
/SWITCH SMF
pause 2

* Prevent new TSO logons
/MODIFY TSO,USERMAX=0
pause 2

* Stop JES2 initiators
/$PI
pause 2

* Stop JES2 output devices
/$P PRT1
/$P PRT2
/$P PRT3
/$P PUNCH1
/$P RDR1
/$P RDR2
pause 3

* Stop TSO
/STOP TSO
pause 3

* Stop VTAM
/HALT NET,QUICK
pause 3
